survey.music_making: took viola from age 10-11 through school, played french horn age 13-15 from school, and in school choir for 5 years. No longer play any instruments, still sing occasionally in private, but not a musician.
survey.medium: Youtube, personal album collection, public library music rentals.
survey.activities: driving, washing dishes, house cleaning, hanging out with friends and family, working on art projects, paying bills and other personal finance tasks, taking a shower/bath.
survey.other_genres: French music, K-Pop (Korean), J-Pop (Japanese), anime themes, video game music, film soundtracks.
survey.habit_change: When I was growing up I mainly listened to classic rock, 80s rock, and classical music because that's what the adults around me enjoyed. I have expanded the types of genres that I expose myself to over the years and enjoy listening to and exploring new types of music.
survey.habits: I like to listen to particular types of music while doing different activities to set the mood. For example, if I'm doing something where I need to focus, like writing or paying bills, I will listen to relaxing instrumental music like light jazz, classical, or bossa nova. But if I'm doing a more physically active activity I like to listen to more upbeat music, like pop or hip hop. I like listening to singer/songwriter music while I shower so I can sing along.
